To take an example ([simd8f.h:160](https://github.com/davisking/dlib/blob/master/dlib/simd/simd8f.h#L160)), the current code:

```cpp
    inline simd8f operator+ (const simd8f& lhs, const simd8f& rhs) 
    { 
#ifdef DLIB_HAVE_AVX
        return _mm256_add_ps(lhs, rhs); 
#else
        return simd8f(lhs.low()+rhs.low(),
                      lhs.high()+rhs.high());
#endif
    }
```

would become:
```cpp
__attribute__ ((target ("default")))
inline simd8f operator+ (const simd8f& lhs, const simd8f& rhs) 
{ 
        return simd8f(lhs.low()+rhs.low(),
                      lhs.high()+rhs.high());
}

__attribute__ ((target ("avx")))
inline simd8f operator+ (const simd8f& lhs, const simd8f& rhs) 
{ 
        return _mm256_add_ps(lhs, rhs);
}
```
``gcc`` would automatically generate the dispatch code so that, *at runtime*, either the default or the AVX versions are used, depending on what the CPU supports.

It is probably necessary to put this code within ``gcc`` fences to maintain portability on VS (so I guess it would simply be easier to have a ``simd8f-multiversioning.h`` version of ``simd8f.h``).

Please note that *I do not* intend to submit pull requests  implementing these changes in the foreseeable future. I opened this issue merely to track possible future feature, relevant to ``dlib``.

