@linkerzhang @anderspapitto  I'm not convinced that BC version bump here was necessary. We're simply adding a new attribute, and its default value (0) matches the old behavior, right? So this is a backwards-compatible change and no version update is necessary. (Of course, it is also semantically valid to do a version update; it just means that you're forcing producers to rev their targeted operator version to take advantage of the new version. Best not to make their life hard.)

Also, technically, you were supposed to increase the max version number here. I'm going to write a bot that will lint these cases.
